article.headline: Princeton 73, Lehigh 64
article.story: PRINCETON, N.J. -- Dan Mavraides scored a game-high 21 points -- including four 3-pointers -- as Princeton beat Lehigh 73-64 on Wednesday. Doug Davis added 14 points for the Tigers (4-8), while Marcus Schroeder finished with 10 points and eight rebounds. Zahir Carrington had 20 points and 11 rebounds for the Mountain Hawks (10-4), while Marquis Hall scored had 11 points. The teams traded baskets for most of the first half before Princeton closed with a 6-0 run to take a 32-28 lead at the break. The Tigers then remained in command for most of the second half, but Lehigh tried to rally late and cut the lead to 65-60 on two free throws by Hall with 1:05 remaining. The Mountain Hawks would not get any closer, though, and Princeton then sealed the win by making 8-of-10 free throws.
